Class SigmaDJProductSimulator

SigmaSimulator
public class SigmaDJProductSimulator
extends java.lang.Object
implements SigmaSimulator

Concrete implementation of Sigma Simulator.

This implementation simulates the case that the prover convince a verifier that 3 ciphertexts c1,c2,c3 are encryptions of values x1,x2,x3 s.t. x1*x2=x3 mod N.

The pseudo code of this protocol can be found in Protocol 1.13 of pseudo codes document at http://crypto.biu.ac.il/scapi/SDK_Pseudocode_SCAPI_V2.0.0.pdf.

Author:
Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Moriya Farbstein)
